# Identity Resolution — local development environment template.
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` (gitignored by repo-root .gitignore) and
# fill in real values. Loaded by:
#
#   • `dotnet run` from a shell that has these exported (e.g. via direnv,
#     `set -a; source .env.local; set +a` in WSL, or `gci env:`-style
#     loading in PowerShell).
#   • VS F5 — duplicate these into `Properties/launchSettings.json` (the
#     IDE does not auto-load .env files).
#
# Variable layout: `IDENTITY__<section>__<key>` — double underscore
# between section and key, section names match the YAML/options classes
# (`mariadb`, `identity`, ...). Mirrors the convention the retired Rust
# stub established so existing operators' env files keep working.
#
# At deploy time the SAME variables are populated from the
# `insight-identity-config` Kubernetes Secret (mounted via
# `envFrom.secretRef` in the chart's Deployment). The umbrella chart emits
# that Secret on install — for standalone helm installs an operator
# pre-creates an equivalent Secret with these keys.

# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# MariaDB connection
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Either one of:
#
#   • `mariadb__url`   — Rust-parity URL form. Recommended for production.
#                        Format: mysql://user:pass@host:port/db (or
#                        mariadb://...). User/pass may be percent-encoded.
#
#   • `mariadb__connection_string` — raw MySqlConnector key-value form.
#                        Use when you need MariaDB-specific options that
#                        the URL shape cannot express (SslMode,
#                        AllowPublicKeyRetrieval, etc.). Tests use this
#                        path because Testcontainers returns KV form.
#
# When both are set, `connection_string` wins.
IDENTITY__mariadb__url=mysql://insight:CHANGE_ME@localhost:3306/identity
# IDENTITY__mariadb__connection_string=Server=localhost;Port=3306;Database=identity;Uid=insight;Pwd=CHANGE_ME

# Optional pool/timeout overrides. Zero / unset = MySqlConnector defaults
# (Pooling=true, MinPoolSize=0, MaxPoolSize=100, ConnectionTimeout=15s,
# CommandTimeout=30s). Set to non-zero ONLY with a measured reason —
# values below ~30s for command_timeout_seconds suffocate the post-handshake
# `SET NAMES` round-trip and surface as `Connect Timeout expired`.
# IDENTITY__mariadb__min_pool_size=0
# IDENTITY__mariadb__max_pool_size=0
# IDENTITY__mariadb__connection_timeout_seconds=0
# IDENTITY__mariadb__command_timeout_seconds=0

# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Identity service
# --------------------------------------------------------------------
# Bind socket. Default 0.0.0.0:8082 in containers; 127.0.0.1 for local
# loopback avoids the Windows Defender Firewall popup on F5.
IDENTITY__identity__bind_addr=127.0.0.1:8082

# Default tenant pinned for header-less callers. Keeps the API behaviour
# identical to the Rust stub (which had no tenant concept at all).
# Replace with the real tenant UUID present in `persons.insight_tenant_id`;
# when in doubt, query:
#   SELECT DISTINCT LOWER(HEX(insight_tenant_id)) FROM persons LIMIT 5;
# Once the api-gateway forwards JWT claims, callers override per-request
# via the `X-Insight-Tenant-Id` header — that always wins over this default.
IDENTITY__identity__tenant_default_id=00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

# Phase 2 toggles — leave off until reconciliation service starts emitting
# `parent_person_id` observations.
# IDENTITY__identity__expand_subordinates=false
# IDENTITY__identity__max_subordinate_depth=5
